<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c654463-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s2607"><num value="2607">§ 2607.</num><heading> Fees</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of Transportation may collect a fee under <ref href="/us/usc/t31/s9701">section 9701 of title 31</ref> of not more than $1,000, from each person to whom a permit is issued under this subchapter for a permitting system and to maintain information.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c654464-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/688/tIV/s4107">Pub. L. 100–688, title IV, § 4107</ref>, <date date="1988-11-18">Nov. 18, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/4158">102 Stat. 4158</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
